  "text": "An overview of our depth image upsampling framework is provided in Fig. 4 , and the proposed algorithm is sketched in Algorithm 1. Once the scaling factor is determined, we use the bicubic interpolation to obtain the initial estimation, and then, guided filter and gradient minimization method are used as follows. Parameter β is automatically adapted in iterations starting from a small value β 0 , and it is multiplied by κ each time. This scheme is inspired by Wang et al. [CITATION_1] , which shows that this scheme is effective to speed up convergence. In all the experiments, we fix the regularization parameters β 0 = 0.0025 and set κ = 2 to balance the efficiency and performance. ",
